<ul>
<li style="list-style-type:none"> </li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><span style="page:WordSection2"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">CTX is generally adequate coverage for aspiration PNA without evidence of abscess, empyema, or cavitary lesion on imaging</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="page:WordSection2"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">There is low sensitivity of S. pneumoniae to azithromycin (42%) and doxycycline (72%), so these should not be used as monotherapy</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="page:WordSection2"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Check for DDI with Linezolid (e.g., SSRI)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
