<ul>
<li style="list-style-type:none">
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type:none"> </li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Duration: 7 days in uncomplicated cases, although specific pathogens (e.g., <i>Pseudomonas</i>) may require longer duration and ID guidance</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Consider ID consultation if the patient is not clinically improving on empiric therapy or if an MDR pathogen grows from culture</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">If no MRSA isolated and pt is improving, consider stopping vancomycin ASAP</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="background:white"><span style="font-family:Palatino"><span style="color:black">Some concern for nephrotoxicity with combination Vancomycin and piperacillin-tazobactam, but data controversial</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
